<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 08 at 10:30PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT CENTRAL SOMERSET COUNTY THROUGH
1115 PM EDT...
At 1030 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southeast of Somerset, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Meyersdale, Berlin, Garrett, Indian Lake, Shanksville, New Baltimore
and Flight 93 National Memorial.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
